        25 February 2022 - 3 March 2022

        The Official Singles Chart Top 100 reflects the UKs biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1. View the biggest songs of 2025.

        Most of this Encanto stuff is a bit annoying, especially the Bruno one! However, I am intrigued: why are there only three? Surely the Official Charts aren't treating 'Encanto' as an artist? They're clearly all by very different artists and if there are three in the top ten then I'd expect some more, even if in very near the bottom of the 100.

        Surface Pressure is growing on me but somewhat undermined by Radio 1's insistence on having such a massively edited version on their show EVERY week. Why is there so much jibberjabber and so little music on that show nowadays? It's so short compared to how it used to be and almost everything is chopped right down. Do people _really_ have such short attention spans these days or are Radio 1 just being really annoying? I suspect mainly the latter, but also a bit of the former.
